## 🎯 SUCCESS METRICS

You're doing this right when:
- User rarely has to say "that's not what I meant"
- Scope freeze document matches actual Phase 1 work
- Code reviews find style issues, not architectural mismatches
- Beads move to "done" without reopening
- Next session can start immediately without archaeology

You're doing this WRONG when:
- Features get built then removed as "not Phase 1"
- User has to explain the same requirement 3 times
- Code contradicts architecture docs
- Sessions end with "I'll finish this next time" (should be atomic bead completions)

